		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>Here's what I came up with, little long I suppose because of the wrappers, but personally I find CFScript much more readable than CFML. :P</p><p>&lt;!---<br>	Simple script to get HTML comments from source code.</p><p>	Method: getCommentsFromCodeOrString()</p><p>	Takes one parameter which is either source code or a URL (http,https)</p><p>	Author: Elliott Sprehn<br>	Date: May 12, 2006<br>	Version: 1.0<br>---&gt;</p><p>&lt;!---<br>	Throw an exception in a script context.</p><p>	@param String type     The type of exception to throw (Default: 'Application')<br>	@param String message  The message for the exception (Default: '');<br>	@param String detail   Detailed error message to show</p><p>	@throws Custom Exception<br>---&gt;<br>&lt;cffunction name="throw"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="type" type="string" required="false" default="Application"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="message" type="string" required="false" default=""&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="detail" type="string" required="false" default=""&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfthrow type="#type#" message="#message#" detail="#detail#"&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p><p>&lt;!---<br>	Really simple wrapper for CFHTTP.</p><p>	@param String url The url to perform a HTTP request on.</p><p>	@return Struct CFHTTP result structure.<br>---&gt;<br>&lt;cffunction name="performHTTPRequest"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="url" type="string" require="true" /&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="timeout" type="numeric" require="false" default="30" /&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfhttp url="#arguments.url#" timeout="#arguments.timeout#" /&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfreturn cfhttp /&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p><p>&lt;!--- <br>	Determines if a URL or source code was specified, if source code was specified<br>	it just returns it, else it performs a HTTP request and grabs the source code <br>	from that website and returns it.</p><p>	@param String data The HTML source code or a URL</p><p>	@throws HTTPConnecitonError Server did not respond<br>	@throws HTTPResponseError   Response body was empty</p><p>	@return string HTML source code<br>---&gt;<br>&lt;cffunction name="getHTMLSourceCode"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="data" type="string" required="true" /&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfscript&gt;<br>		var http = '';</p><p>		if( REFindNoCase("^(http://|https://).+",Form.Data) ) {</p><p>			http = performHTTPRequest( Form.Data );</p><p>			if( http.ErrorDetail NEQ "" ) {</p><p>				throw("HTTPConnectionError",<br>					  "Failed to connect to server.",<br>					  http.ErrorDetail );<br>			}</p><p>			if( http.text ) {</p><p>				return http.FileContent;</p><p>			} else {</p><p>				throw("HTTPResponseError",<br>					  "No response text from server.",<br>					  "Status code returned: " &amp; local.http.responseheader.Status_Code );<br>			}</p><p>		} else {</p><p>			return Form.Data;<br>		}<br>	&lt;/cfscript&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p><p>&lt;!--- <br>	Parse out the source string for comments returning an array of them.</p><p>	@param String SourceCode The source code to parse.</p><p>	@return Array Array of comments.<br>---&gt;<br>&lt;cffunction name="getHTMLCommentsFromCode"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="sourceCode" type="string" required="true" /&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfscript&gt;<br>		var results = ArrayNew(1);<br>		var offset = 0;<br>		var matchStart = 0;<br>		var matchEnd = 0;</p><p>		while( offset LT Len(arguments.sourceCode) ) {</p><p>			matchStart = FindNoCase("&lt;!--",arguments.sourceCode, offset );</p><p>			if( matchStart NEQ 0 ) {</p><p>				matchEnd = FindNoCase("--&gt;",arguments.sourceCode,matchStart);</p><p>				ArrayAppend(results,Mid(arguments.sourceCode,matchStart + 4,matchEnd - MatchStart - 4) );<br>				offset = matchEnd + 4;</p><p>			} else {</p><p>				break;<br>			}<br>		}</p><p>		return results;<br>	&lt;/cfscript&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p><p>&lt;!--- <br>	Gets an array of comments from either a string of HTML source or a URL.</p><p>	@param String codeOrString The code or URL</p><p>	@return Array An Array of comments from the source or false if failure<br>---&gt;<br>&lt;cffunction name="getCommentsFromCodeOrString"&gt;<br>	&lt;cfargument name="codeOrString" type="string" required="true"&gt;</p><p>	&lt;cfscript&gt;<br>		var SourceCode = '';</p><p>		try {<br>			SourceCode = getHTMLSourceCode( Arguments.codeOrString );</p><p>		// bad response error<br>		} catch( HTTPResponseError e ) {</p><p>			WriteOutput("Server response had no body!");<br>			return false;</p><p>		// connection failure<br>		} catch( HTTPConnectionError e ) {</p><p>			WriteOutput("Connection failure: #Arguments.codeOrString#");<br>			return false;<br>		}</p><p>		return getHTMLCommentsFromCode( SourceCode );<br>	&lt;/cfscript&gt;<br>&lt;/cffunction&gt;</p></div>
